1. Introduction
Welcome to Surfcheck's Privacy Policy. We highly value the protection of your privacy and personal data. This Privacy Policy has been created to inform you about how we handle the personal data we collect through our apps and websites. We kindly request you to carefully review this Privacy Policy.
Al our services are also bound to our terms of use,
download this PDF with our terms of use
to view these.
2. Data Collection
Surfcheck collects various types of data to provide and improve our services. This data may include:
Personal identification information (such as name, email address)
Usage data (such as pages visited, click behaviour)
Device information (such as IP address, browser type)
Location data (if you grant permission)
3. Use of Data
The collected data is used for the following purposes:
Providing and improving our services
Personalising your experience
Analysing the use of our apps and websites
Displaying relevant advertisements (where applicable)
Communicating with you about updates, offers, and news
4. Data Sharing
Surfcheck does not share your data with third parties unless it is necessary for providing our services or legally required. In some cases, we may share data with:
Service providers who assist us in analysing usage data
Advertising partners (only if you use apps or websites with advertisements)
Law enforcement agencies if legally required
5. Security
We take the security of your data seriously and have implemented appropriate technical and organisational measures to protect your data against unauthorised access, loss, or theft. These measures are regularly evaluated and updated where necessary.
6. Cookies and Similar Technologies
Our apps and websites use cookies and similar technologies to enhance your experience and help us analyse the use of our services. You can adjust your cookie settings through your browser or device settings.
7. Your Rights and Choices
You have various rights regarding your personal data, insofar as it is processed by us and not by external providers, including:
The right to access your data
The right to correct inaccurate data
The right to delete your data
The right to object to certain forms of data processing
To exercise these rights, you can contact us using the contact details at the end of this Privacy Policy.
8. Children's Privacy
Our services are not intended for children under the age of 16. We do not knowingly collect data from children under this age. If you suspect that we have inadvertently collected data from a minor, please contact us so we can take appropriate measures.
9. Changes to the Privacy Policy
We reserve the right to modify this Privacy Policy from time to time. Changes will be published on this page, and if necessary, we will inform you about this via email or a notification in our apps.
10. Contact
If you have any questions, comments, or requests regarding this Privacy Policy or the way we handle your data, you can contact us at:
Surfcheck
Rijn en Schiekade 115 F, 2311 AS Leiden
post@surfcheck.info
(+31) 071-2032041